// M0 milestone — codegen broadening (Gap 15) source fixture.
//
// This is the user-facing hexa source the codegen must lower. The
// compiler driver (compiler/main.hexa) currently aborts at
// type-check before reaching codegen on real source (see
// doc/stage1_punch_list.md Gaps 1–10), so direct end-to-end
// compilation of this file does not yet succeed. Verification of
// the codegen path runs out of tests/m0/concat_test.hexa, which
// hand-builds the equivalent MIR and asserts the produced .s
// contains:
//   - a `.LCstr0` rodata entry holding the bytes of "hi "
//   - a call to the runtime stub `hexa_str_concat`
//   - the AAPCS64 / System V arg-marshal mov-pairs into x0/x1
//     (arm64) or rdi/rsi (x86_64) ahead of the call.
//
// Once Gaps 1–10 land and compiler/main.hexa reaches codegen, this
// file will be the canonical end-to-end concat smoke source.
fn greet(name: string) -> string {
    return "hi " + name
}
